<subSubSection pageId="74" pageNumber="469" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="74.[1392,2599,1958,2693]" pageId="74" pageNumber="469">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1395,1745,2422,2455]" pageId="74" pageNumber="469">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Kongana Forest Shrew occurs in Dzanga-Sangha Forest Reserve in south-western Central African Republic and Moukalaba-Doudou National Park in Gabon. It is probably very rare because it occurred in only 1-:3% of 311 small carnivore scats collected in Dzanga-Sangha and represented only 0-8% of 1350 shrews captured in Ngotto Forest, Central African Republic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
